1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,170
She went on to say, there is shocking evidence that millions of other people are killing themselves by slower,

2
00:00:07,280 --> 00:00:09,010
less obvious methods.

3
00:00:09,280 --> 00:00:19,810
Still others are committing spiritual rather than physical suicide, constantly seeking out ways to humiliate, punish, and generally diminish themselves.

4
00:00:20,560 --> 00:00:29,569
The psychologist friend mentioned before told me how he helped one of his patients to stop committing mental and spiritual suicide.

5
00:00:29,920 --> 00:00:34,609
This patient, he explained, was in her late thirties and had two children.

6
00:00:34,800 --> 00:00:38,849
In lay terminology, she suffered from severe depression.

7
00:00:39,120 --> 00:00:43,970
She looked back on every incident of her life as being an unhappy experience.

8
00:00:44,160 --> 00:00:51,410
Her school days, her marriage, the bearing of her children, the places she had lived, all were thought of negatively.

9
00:00:51,680 --> 00:00:56,290
She volunteered that she couldn't remember ever having been truly happy.

10
00:00:56,400 --> 00:01:01,250
And since what one remembers from the past colors what one sees in the present,

11
00:01:01,440 --> 00:01:04,369
she saw nothing but pessimism and darkness.

12
00:01:04,960 --> 00:01:09,010
When I asked her what she saw in a picture which I showed her,

13
00:01:09,040 --> 00:01:13,569
she said, it looks like there will be a terrible thunderstorm tonight.

14
00:01:14,079 --> 00:01:18,450
That was the gloomiest interpretation of the picture I've yet heard.

15
00:01:18,640 --> 00:01:25,089
The picture was a large oil painting of the sun low in the sky and a jagged rocky coastline.

16
00:01:25,200 --> 00:01:31,569
The painting was very cleverly done and could be construed to be either a sunrise or a sunset.

17
00:01:31,760 --> 00:01:38,369
The psychologist commented to me that what a person sees in the picture is a clue to his personality.

18
00:01:38,560 --> 00:01:46,849
Most people say it is a sunrise, but the depressed, mentally disturbed person nearly always says it's a sunset.

19
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:52,690
As a psychologist, I can't change what already is in a person's memory.

20
00:01:52,800 --> 00:01:59,410
But I can, with the patient's cooperation, help the individual to see his past in a different light.

21
00:01:59,680 --> 00:02:03,010
That's the general treatment I used on this woman.

